# =============================================================================
# backend/.dockerignore
# =============================================================================
# Added after discovering .env, .env.docker, venv/, db.sqlite3, and
# media/ were all being copied into every image via `COPY . .` with
# no exclusions. Two separate problems this fixes:
#   1. Secrets (.env*) baked permanently into image layer history —
#      the actual reason this file exists at all.
#   2. Dead weight (venv/, db.sqlite3, media/) bloating every single
#      build for no runtime benefit — venv/ especially, since the
#      Dockerfile already does its own pip install; the copied one
#      is never used.
# =============================================================================

# ── Secrets — never bake these into an image layer ─────────────
.env
.env.docker
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Local dev artifacts — meaningless inside a container ───────
venv/
env/
.venv/
db.sqlite3
db.sqlite3-journal
*.pyc
__pycache__/
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
*.log

# ── Volume-mounted at runtime — don't duplicate into the image ─
media/

# ── VCS / editor / OS noise ──────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store

# ── Anything Docker-related itself — no reason to be in the
#    build context of the image it's building ──────────────────
Dockerfile
docker-compose*.yml
.dockerignore
